        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:00PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Camp Dennison,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Murdock, Blue Ash, Camp Dennison, Day Heights, The Village of Indian
Hill, Sixteen Mile Stand, Dallasburg, Terrace Park, Morrow,
Rossmoyne, Springvale, Edenton, Pleasant Plain, Remington,
Plainville, Mulberry, Milford, Montgomery, Newtonsville, and
Butlerville.

This includes I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 12 and 17.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for
southwestern Ohio. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in effect
until 900 PM EDT for southwestern Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
